# Global Audit Memory

## Scope Touched
- `LayerZero/CrossChainRouter.sol` - remains primary hotspot; cross-chain borrow/liquidation handlers, packet/processability checks, `srcEid`/`destEid` binding, and seize-domain consistency repeatedly probed.
- `LayerZero/CoreRouter.sol` - heavy review of borrow/redeem/liquidation execution ordering, liquidity/risk checks under potentially stale accrual state, and router↔storage state transition correctness.
- `LayerZero/LendStorage.sol` - recurring focus on borrow-index/principal/debt coherence, liquidity/accounting reads, cross-chain record lookup (`findCrossChain`), and reward/distribution bookkeeping edge cases.
- `LayerZero/interaces/*.sol` (`LendInterface.sol`, `LendtrollerInterfaceV2.sol`, plus broader interface assumptions) - touched mainly as schema/wiring context; interface-level assumption pressure still relatively light.
- `Lendtroller.sol` - still mostly contextual reference for collateral/liquidation assumptions rather than deep standalone analysis.

## Issue Directions Seen
- Cross-chain accounting drift across `CrossChainRouter`/`CoreRouter`/`LendStorage` (principal, debt, index, and key/domain attribution coherence).
- Non-atomic cross-chain lifecycle failures (message finalization gaps, packet unprocessability, receive-path mismatch windows).
- Liquidation consistency risks: market mapping/validation, seize-vs-repay domain or chain-ID mismatch, close-factor realism vs accrued debt.
- Stale-state risk checks in liquidity/collateral validation (accrual timing and state freshness).
- Repay/liquidation ordering and cleanup transition hazards (including reentrancy-style sequencing concerns).
- Economic/config side paths: LayerZero fee handling plus protocol reward accrual/distribution/withdrawability and division-by-zero surfaces.

## Useful Context
- Round 14 again concentrated on the same core trio (`CrossChainRouter.sol`, `CoreRouter.sol`, `LendStorage.sol`), with strongest overlap on cross-chain liquidation/borrow handling.
- New candidate set (`F-046` to `F-050`) was proposed but not retained; this continues to indicate unresolved ambiguity, not demonstrated safety.
- Attention split in R14: one track emphasized stale accrual + packet/processability in liquidation; the other emphasized reward/distribution edge cases and chain-ID/index consistency breadth.
- `LayerZero/interaces` path typo still appears in repo/audit traces and can skew search/navigation coverage.
